{"title_page": "Zar Randeri", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox writer  \n| name = Zar Randeri<br/>\n\u0a9d\u0abe\u0ab0 \u0ab0\u0abe\u0a82\u0aa6\u0ac7\u0ab0\u0ac0\n| image =\n| caption = \n| native_name = \u0aad\u0ab0\u0ac1\u0a9a\u0abe \u0ab9\u0abe\u0ab8\u0abf\u0aae\u0aac\u0abf\u0aa8 \u0aaf\u0ac1\u0ab8\u0ac1\u0aab\n| native_name_lang = gu\n| pseudonym = Zar Randeri\n| birth_name = Bharucha Hasim bin Yusuf\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1887|11|1|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rander]], [[Surat]], [[Gujarat]]\n| resting_place = \n| occupation = Poet, Translator\n| language = [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]]\n| nationality = [[India]]n\n| education = \n| alma_mater = \n| movement = \n| notablework = ''Shairi'' 1 - 2 (1936)\n| spouse = \n| awards = \n| signature = \n| years_active = \n}}\n'''Bharucha Hasim bin Yusuf''' ({{lang-gu|\u0aad\u0ab0\u0ac1\u0a9a\u0abe \u0ab9\u0abe\u0ab8\u0abf\u0aae\u0aac\u0abf\u0aa8 \u0aaf\u0ac1\u0ab8\u0ac1\u0aab}}), better known by his pen name '''Zar Randeri''' ({{lang-gu|\u0a9d\u0abe\u0ab0 \u0ab0\u0abe\u0a82\u0aa6\u0ac7\u0ab0\u0ac0}}), was a [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]] poet and translator from [[Gujarat]], [[India]].<ref name= \"zr\">{{cite encyclopedia |last=Dave |first=Ramesh R. |editor-last=Topiwala |editor-first=Chandrakant |editor-link= Chandrakant Topiwala|encyclopedia=Gujarati Sahityakosh (Encyclopedia of Gujarati Literature) |title=Bharucha Hasim bin Yusuf |language= Gujarati |year=1990 |publisher=[[Gujarati Sahitya Parishad]] |volume=2 |location=Ahmedabad |pages=427}}</ref> He was born in [[Rander]], a town in [[Surat]], [[Gujarat]]. He received his primary and secondary education in Rander and then went to Aminiyah Arabiyah, a [[Madrasa]] in [[Delhi]], for further education. He published the first Gujarati book on Persian [[Arabic prosody|metres]]<ref name=\"Datta 2016\">{{cite web | last=Datta | first=Amaresh | title=Encyclopaedia of Indian Literature | website=Google Books | date=2016-07-28 | url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Encyclopaedia_of_Indian_Literature.html?id=zB4n3MVozbUC | accessdate=2016-08-11}}</ref> as ''Shairi'' in two volumes in 1936. His other notable works include ''Shamshire Sadakat'', ''Hindustan Na Humla'', ''Aatma Ane Punarjanma''. He translated and published several works such as ''Kasdussabil'' (1913), ''Muhannad'', ''Dharmaprachar'', ''Mahatma Ane Islam'' and ''Hindustani Bhasha''.<ref name= \"zr\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Randeri, Zar}}\n[[Category:Gujarati-language writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian poets]]\n[[Category:People from Surat district]]\n[[Category:Gujarati-language poets]]\n[[Category:Poets from Gujarat]]\n[[Category:1887 births]]\n[[Category:Indian male poets]]\n[[Category:Date of death missing]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male writers]]\n\n\n{{India-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox writer  \n| name = Zar Randeri<br/>\n\u0a9d\u0abe\u0ab0 \u0ab0\u0abe\u0a82\u0aa6\u0ac7\u0ab0\u0ac0\n| image =\n| caption = \n| native_name = \u0aad\u0ab0\u0ac1\u0a9a\u0abe \u0ab9\u0abe\u0ab8\u0abf\u0aae\u0aac\u0abf\u0aa8 \u0aaf\u0ac1\u0ab8\u0ac1\u0aab\n| native_name_lang = gu\n| pseudonym = Zar Randeri\n| birth_name = Bharucha Hasim bin Yusuf\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1887|11|1|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rander]], [[Surat]], [[Gujarat]]\n| resting_place = \n| occupation = Poet, Translator\n| language = [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]]\n| nationality = [[India]]n\n| education = \n| alma_mater = \n| movement = \n| notablework = ''Shairi'' 1 - 2 (1936)\n| spouse = \n| awards = \n| signature = \n| years_active = \n}}\n'''Bharucha Hasim bin Yusuf''' ({{lang-gu|\u0aad\u0ab0\u0ac1\u0a9a\u0abe \u0ab9\u0abe\u0ab8\u0abf\u0aae\u0aac\u0abf\u0aa8 \u0aaf\u0ac1\u0ab8\u0ac1\u0aab}}), better known by his pen name '''Zar Randeri''' ({{lang-gu|\u0a9d\u0abe\u0ab0 \u0ab0\u0abe\u0a82\u0aa6\u0ac7\u0ab0\u0ac0}}), was a [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]] poet and translator from [[Gujarat]], [[India]].<ref name= \"zr\">{{cite encyclopedia |last=Dave |first=Ramesh R. |editor-last=Topiwala |editor-first=Chandrakant |editor-link= Chandrakant Topiwala|encyclopedia=Gujarati Sahityakosh (Encyclopedia of Gujarati Literature) |title=Bharucha Hasim bin Yusuf |language= Gujarati |year=1990 |publisher=[[Gujarati Sahitya Parishad]] |volume=2 |location=Ahmedabad |pages=427}}</ref> He was born in [[Rander]], a town in [[Surat]], [[Gujarat]]. He received his primary and secondary education in Rander and then went to Aminiyah Arabiyah, a [[Madrasa]] in [[Delhi]], for further education. He published the first Gujarati book on Persian [[Arabic prosody|metres]]<ref name=\"Datta 2016\">{{cite web | last=Datta | first=Amaresh | title=Encyclopaedia of Indian Literature | website=Google Books | date=2016-07-28 | url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Encyclopaedia_of_Indian_Literature.html?id=zB4n3MVozbUC | accessdate=2016-08-11}}</ref> as ''Shairi'' in two volumes in 1936. His other notable works include ''Shamshire Sadakat'', ''Hindustan Na Humla'', ''Aatma Ane Punarjanma''. He translated and published several works such as ''Kasdussabil'' (1913), ''Muhannad'', ''Dharmaprachar'', ''Mahatma Ane Islam'' and ''Hindustani Bhasha''.<ref name= \"zr\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Randeri, Zar}}\n[[Category:Gujarati-language writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian poets]]\n[[Category:People from Surat district]]\n[[Category:Gujarati-language poets]]\n[[Category:Poets from Gujarat]]\n[[Category:1887 births]]\n[[Category:Indian male poets]]\n[[Category:Date of death missing]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male writers]]\n\n\n{{India-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zar_Randeri"}
{"title_page": "Jahrom", "text_new": "{{for|the administrative subdivision|Jahrom County}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name =Jahrom\n|native_name = \u062c\u0647\u0631\u0645\n| nickname                        =The Green Umbrella, Dar ol-Momenin, City of Sour Gold, Land of Palms and Oranges\n|settlement_type        = City\n|image_skyline =jahrom wiews.jpg\n|imagesize =250px\n|image_caption = from top to bottom, left to right : [[Sangtarashan cave]], Jahrom bazaar, Jahrom fire temple (Qadamgah), Chamran square, Emamzadeh Hossein, Jahrom skyline\n|pushpin_map            =Iran\n|mapsize                =150px\n|subdivision_type       = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}}\n|subdivision_type1 =[[Provinces of Iran|Province]]\n|subdivision_name1 =[[Fars Province|Fars]]\n|subdivision_type2 =[[Counties of Iran|County]]\n|subdivision_name2 =[[Jahrom County|Jahrom]]\n|subdivision_type3 =[[Bakhsh]]\n|subdivision_name3 =[[Central District (Jahrom County)|Central]]\n|leader_title           = \n|leader_name            = \n|established_title      =\n|established_date       = \n|area_total_km2         = 30\n| area_rank = 2nd\n|area_footnotes         = \n|population_as_of       = 2016 Census\n|population_urban       = 141,634 <ref>https://www.amar.org.ir/english</ref>\n| population_blank1_title         = Population Rank\n| population_blank1               = 3rd\n|population_est         =\n|population_est_as_of   =\n|population_density_km2   =4,754\n|timezone               = [[Iran Standard Time|IRST]]\n|utc_offset             = +3:30\n|timezone_DST           = [[Iran Daylight Time|IRDT]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +4:30\n|coordinates            = {{coord|28|30|00|N|53|33|38|E|region:IR|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_m              = 1050\n|website                  = {{URL|jahrom.ir}}\n|area_code =  \n|footnotes              =\n}}\n'''Jahrom''' ({{lang-fa|\u062c\u0647\u0631\u0645}}, also known as '''Jahr\u016bm''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3067522}}</ref> is a city and capital of [[Jahrom County]], [[Fars Province]], [[Iran]].  At the 2016 census, its population was 141,634.<ref>{{IranCensus2016|07}}</ref> Jahrom is the biggest city in the southern half of Fars Province and the second one in whole province.<ref>{{IranCensus2016|07}}</ref>\n\nJahrom is located {{convert|170|km|mi}} southeast of [[Shiraz, Iran|Shiraz]], the [[Capital (political)|capital]] of Fars Province. Jahrom has a [[hot semi-arid climate]] and the average rainfall is about {{convert|285|mm|in}} per year. The average temperature in this city is about {{convert|20|C|F}}. The maximum temperature in summer reaches {{convert|45|C|F}} and the minimum temperature in winter reaches {{convert|-5|C|F}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.farsmet.ir/DM/Files/files/jahrom.pdf |title=Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Fars province Meteorological Organization |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref> The average height of Jahrom is about  {{convert|1050|m|ft}} above sea level. The majority of people in Jahrom are [[Persians]] and [[Shia Islam|Shia Muslims]].\n\nJahrom is one of the historical cities of Iran. The founder of the city of Jahrom, [[Artaxerxes I of Persia]], the son of [[Xerxes I]], the fifth [[Achaemenid Empire|Achaemenid king]]. [[Ferdosi]] has mentioned Jahrom many times in [[Shahnameh]], especially in the stories related to [[Ardashir I]]. There are many ancient monuments and tourist attractions in Jahrom, Such as [[Sangtarashan cave]], [[Jameh Mosque of Jahrom]], Jahrom bazaar, Khan school and fire temple of Jahrom (Qadamgah).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fafarschto.ir/ |title=Cultural Heritage, Handicrafts and Tourism Organization of Fars province |last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nJahrom, with several universities, hospitals and medical centers, is one of the academic and medical hubs of [[southern Iran]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://snn.ir/fa/news/415249/%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%82%D8%B7%D8%A8-%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%AA-%D8%AC%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A8-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%AF%DB%8C%D9%84-%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%AF |title=Jahrom is the health center of the south |last= |first= |date= |website=Students News Network (SNN) |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref> Jahrom has two industrial towns, a special economic zone, a [[dry port]], a [[petrochemical plant]], an [[Jahrom Airport|airport]], an [[Islamic Republic of Iran Broadcasting|IRIB]] center, [[customs]] and a [[combined cycle power plant]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idro.ir/fa-ir/ActivityScopes/EconomicZones/Pages/Jahrom.aspx |title= Jahrom special economic zone|last= |first= |date= |website=Industrial Development and Renovation Organization of Iran (IDRO) |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref> Jahrom has special governorate and the municipality of the city is the second municipality in Fars province in terms of history of establishment and degree of municipality after Shiraz.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://shiraze.ir/fa/news/42176/%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D9%88%DB%8C%DA%98%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%A7-%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%AA |title= Jahrom's governorate upgraded to special |last= |first= |date= |website=Shiraze |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623143007/http://www.imo.org.ir/files/rimo-ir//PDF/Unzip_amardaraje.zip/amardarajeNew/fars.pdf |title=population and year of establishment of cities in Fars province |last= |first= |date= |website=Organization of Municipalities of Iran |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nJahrom's economy is based on agriculture and industry, and its most important agricultural products are [[date (fruit)|date]]s and [[citrus]]. Jahrom produces %1.2 of the world's dates and %6 percent of its citrus fruits every year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.irna.ir/news/80543857/%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%83%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%87-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D9%86%DA%AF%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA |title= citrus of Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mehrnews.com/news/3864142/%D8%AC%D9%86%DA%AF%D9%84-%D9%86%D8%AE%D9%84-%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B3-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%87-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%87-%D9%86%D8%AE%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85 |title=dates of Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Mehr news |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n==Name==\nThere are three theories about the name Jahrom:\n*Based on [[Kar-Namag i Ardashir i Pabagan]], in which Jahrom is mentioned as \"Zarham\";  It is probable that Jahrom means \"green space\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Jahrom' |website=Encyclopedia Iranica |url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/jahrom |access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n*Based on [[Ahmad Kasravi]], the late Iranian historians and philologist, the name Jahrom can be analyzed to render a \"warm-place\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.jahrom.org/htmls/history.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2009-12-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110206155148/http://www.jahrom.org/htmls/history.html |archive-date=2011-02-06 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*Jahrom is Consists of \"Ja\" and \"Hrom\", Ja means \"place\" and \"Hrom\" in Avestan means \"high and forbidden fortress\", which is other name of the city of Barzeh (the current [[Takht-e Soleym\u0101n]]) In [[Iranian Azerbaijan]], near the city of [[Maragheh]].\n=== nicknames ===\n\"Green umbrella\" is a nickname of Jahrom due to the resemblance of the huge masses of palm trees around Jahrom to green umbrellas.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iranboom.ir/gardesh-gari/17419-jahrom-980127-027.html |title=Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Iran Boom |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref> \"Dar ol-Momenin\" is the other nickname which means \"house of faithfuls\" because of high percentage of Islam believers in the city. \nJahrom is also known as the \"City of Sour Gold\" and the \"Land of Palms and Oranges\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.farsnews.ir/amp/13910725001135 |title=Jahrom must stay faithful |last= |first= |date= |website=Fars news |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:\u0642\u062f\u0645\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u062c\u0647\u0631\u0645.JPG|220px|thumb|right|Qadamgah in Jahrom]]\nJahrom's history goes back some 2500 years when the [[Achaemenid]]s established the [[Persian Empire]]. The establishment of the city is attributed to [[Artaxerxes I of Persia]]. The [[Sassanid]] monument of Qadamg\u0101h is located to the south of the city , experts believe the monument was constructed during the late Sasanian dynastic era (224-651 AD), and it was a Zoroastrian shrine, probably a fire temple. Jahrom is the birthplace of [[Barbod]], who became the main lyricist and musician in the court of the great Sassanid king [[Khosrau II]] (Parviz).\n\nJahrom was [[Muslim conquest of Persia|conquered by the Muslims]] in 641 or 644 after a fierce battle. \"The Valley of the Martyrs\" in west of the city was the site of this battle, which is why it is called so. As it is described in [[Fars-Nama]], Jahrom's taxes were paid to the Crown Prince during the [[Buyid]] period. In the late [[Safavid]] and early [[Zand dynasty|Zand]] periods, was the start date of planting trees in Jahrom, specially [[Arecaceae|palm]] trees.\n\nDuring the [[Qajar]] period, the ruler of this city began to build buildings and places for urban affairs, including the construction of the bazaar, as well as numerous caravanserais and the development of the city. In 1887, Mohammad Hassan Mirza Mohandes, introduced Jahrom as the largest and most prosperous city in Persia after [[Shiraz]] and [[Bushehr]]. Etemad os-Saltanah describes Jahrom in the late [[Qajar]] period a larger city than cities like [[Qom]] and [[Kashan]].<ref name=\"encyclopedia\">{{cite web | url=https://rch.ac.ir/article/Details/7739 | title=Jahrom | publisher=Islamic World Encyclopedia | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> People of Jahrom had an important rule in [[tobacco protest]]s of 1890 and [[Persian Constitutional Revolution]] of ealry 20th century. [[Abd al-Husayn Najafi Lari]] was the Islamic leader of the city in this period.\n\nJahrom also had an important role in the [[Islamic revolution of Iran]] and was one of the 11 cities with [[Martial law]] in pre-revolution protests. [[Seyyed Hossein ayatollahi]] was the Islamic leader of Jahrom in that period. A soldier killed the military governor of Jahrom on the birthday of [[Mohammad Reza Pahlavi]] on October 6, 1978. 1,200 people of Jahrom were martyred during [[Iran\u2013Iraq War]].<ref name=\"mehromah\">{{cite web | url=http://home.mehromah.ir/fun/touring-iran/4010-Urban-arranged-in-the-East-Empire-of-Ardashir.html | title=Jahrom, a city in the east of Ardeshir's empire | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Martyrs\">{{cite web | url=https://defapress.ir/fa/news/225110/%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%B4%D9%87%D8%B1%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%A8%D8%A7-11-%D8%B4%D9%87%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%82%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%A8 | title=Jahrom county with 11 Martyrs | publisher=Defa press | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Climate==\nJahrom has a [[hot semi-arid climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]]: ''BSh''); The average rainfall is about {{convert|285|mm|in}} per year. The average temperature in this city is about {{convert|20|C|F}}. The maximum temperature in summer reaches {{convert|45|C|F}} and the minimum temperature in winter reaches {{convert|-5|C|F}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.farsmet.ir/DM/Files/files/jahrom.pdf |title=Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Fars province Meteorological Organization |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n{{Weather box\n|width=auto\n|location = Jahrom\n|metric first=yes\n|single line=yes\n|Jan record high C = 20\n|Feb record high C = 23\n|Mar record high C = 27\n|Apr record high C = 34\n|May record high C = 37\n|Jun record high C = 41\n|Jul record high C = 42\n|Aug record high C = 40\n|Sep record high C = 39\n|Oct record high C = 33\n|Nov record high C = 30\n|Dec record high C = 24\n|year record high C = 42\n|Jan high C = 9\n|Feb high C = 13\n|Mar high C = 17\n|Apr high C = 23\n|May high C = 29\n|Jun high C = 34\n|Jul high C = 36\n|Aug high C = 36\n|Sep high C = 32\n|Oct high C = 26\n|Nov high C = 19\n|Dec high C = 13\n|year high C = 24\n|Jan mean C = 6\n|Feb mean C = 8\n|Mar mean C = 12\n|Apr mean C = 17\n|May mean C = 23\n|Jun mean C = 28\n|Jul mean C = 31\n|Aug mean C = 29\n|Sep mean C = 26\n|Oct mean C = 20\n|Nov mean C = 13\n|Dec mean C = 9\n|year mean C = 18\n|Jan low C = 1\n|Feb low C = 3\n|Mar low C = 7\n|Apr low C = 12\n|May low C = 17\n|Jun low C = 22\n|Jul low C = 24\n|Aug low C = 23\n|Sep low C = 19\n|Oct low C = 13\n|Nov low C = 7\n|Dec low C = 4\n|year low C = 13\n|Jan record low C = -12\n|Feb record low C = -8\n|Mar record low C = -3\n|Apr record low C = -2\n|May record low C = 7\n|Jun record low C = 11\n|Jul record low C = 16\n|Aug record low C = 13\n|Sep record low C = 7\n|Oct record low C = 3\n|Nov record low C = -5\n|Dec record low C = -5\n|year record low C = -12\n|precipitation colour = green\n|Jan precipitation mm = 67.2\n|Feb precipitation mm = 64.7\n|Mar precipitation mm = 41.4\n|Apr precipitation mm = 28.8\n|May precipitation mm = 5.1\n|Jun precipitation mm = 0.3\n|Jul precipitation mm = 0.6\n|Aug precipitation mm = 3.5\n|Sep precipitation mm = 0.9\n|Oct precipitation mm = 0.9\n|Nov precipitation mm = 11.0\n|Dec precipitation mm = 60.3\n|year precipitation mm = 284.7\n|unit precipitation days = 1.0 mm\n|Jan precipitation days = 10\n|Feb precipitation days = 8\n|Mar precipitation days = 7\n|Apr precipitation days = 5\n|May precipitation days = 2\n|Jun precipitation days = 0\n|Jul precipitation days = 0\n|Aug precipitation days = 0\n|Sep precipitation days = 0\n|Oct precipitation days = 2\n|Nov precipitation days = 3\n|Dec precipitation days = 7\n|year precipitation days = 44\n|Jan humidity = 64\n|Feb humidity = 62\n|Mar humidity = 57\n|Apr humidity = 51\n|May humidity = 40\n|Jun humidity = 31\n|Jul humidity = 30\n|Aug humidity = 32\n|Sep humidity = 34\n|Oct humidity = 37\n|Nov humidity = 48\n|Dec humidity = 60\n|year humidity = 46\n|Jan sun = 212.6\n|Feb sun = 223.9\n|Mar sun = 239.1\n|Apr sun = 263.5\n|May sun = 310.8\n|Jun sun = 349.1\n|Jul sun = 334.7\n|Aug sun = 323.5\n|Sep sun = 325.2\n|Oct sun = 297.5\n|Nov sun = 253.0\n|Dec sun = 214.2\n|year sun = 3347.0\n|source=Fars province Meteorological Organization<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.farsmet.ir/DM/Files/files/jahrom.pdf |title=Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Fars province Meteorological Organization |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n|accessdate=}}\n\n==Demographics==\n===Population===\n{{Population pyramid\n|year=2010\n|m0=3.7 |m5=3.4 |m10=3.6 |m15=4.3 |m20=6.0 |m25=6.4 |m30=4.5 |m35=3.4 |m40=3.3 |m45=3.0 |m50=2.6 |m55=2.1 |m60=1.3 |m65=1.0 |m70=0.7 |m75=0.6 |m80=0.4 |m85=0.4 \n|f0=3.5 |f5=3.2 |f10=3.5 |f15=4.0 |f20=5.8 |f25=6.1 |f30=4.7 |f35=3.5 |f40=3.3 |f45=2.9 |f50=2.4 |f55=1.9 |f60=1.3 |f65=1.0 |f70=0.7 |f75=0.6 |f80=0.4 |f85=0.4 \n|mmax=6.4\n|fmax=6.1\n}}\n{{As of|2016}}, Jahrom has a population of 141,634. Jahrom is the biggest city in the southern half of [[Fars Province]], the third one in whole province and 67th biggest city of [[Iran]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.citypopulation.de/Iran.html|title=Iran \u2013 City Population \u2013 Cities, Towns & Provinces \u2013 Statistics & Map|publisher=Citypopulation.de|date=3 November 2010|accessdate=5 May 2011}}</ref>\n[[File:JAHROM Population Change-ENG.jpg|thumb|left|230px|Jahrom population change]]\n{{Historical populations|1966|39354|1976|50333|1986|83478|1991|96690|1996|103627|2006|116562|2011|127159|2016|141634|align=center}}\n\n===Ethnics===\nThe main ethnic group in Jahrom constitutes of [[Persian people|Persians]], while  [[Basseri]]es and [[Iranian Arabs|Arabs]] constitute small minorities. They had nomadic life and later [[sedentism]].<ref>P. Oberling, \"F\u0100RS vii. Ethnography\", Encyclopaedia Iranica>{{cite web|url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/fars-vii|title=F\u0100RS vii. Ethnography|date=31 May 2014}}</ref> Due to the geographical characteristics of Jahrom, specially good Rangeland for nomads, Jahrom has long been a residing area for these nomadic peoples.\n\n===Religion===\nThe majority of city are [[Shia Islam|Shia Muslims]], but there is also a small Immigrant [[Sunni Islam|Sunni]] minority in the city.<ref>Persian wikipedia</ref>\n\n==Economic==\n[[File:Nirugahe jahrom.jpg|250px|thumb|right|Jahrom combined cycle power plant]]\nJahrom's economic is based on agriculture. there are 350,000 [[Arecaceae|palm trees]] and 5.3 million [[citrus]] trees in Jahrom which makes Jahrom an agricultural pole in [[Iran]]. Jahrom produces %1.2 of the world's dates and %6 percent of its citrus fruits every year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.irna.ir/news/80543857/%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%83%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%87-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D9%86%DA%AF%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA |title= citrus of Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mehrnews.com/news/3864142/%D8%AC%D9%86%DA%AF%D9%84-%D9%86%D8%AE%D9%84-%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B3-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%87-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%87-%D9%86%D8%AE%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85 |title=dates of Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Mehr news |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nJahrom also has several factories including flour, dairy, brick, rug, plaster, plastic, jam, lemon juice, macaroni and cake factory.<ref>Persian wikipedia</ref>\n\n===Infrastructures===\n*Jahrom combined cycle power plant\n*Jahrom Petrochemistry\n*Jahrom especial economic zone\n*Jahrom economic town\n*Kosar economic town<ref>http://www.idro.ir/fa-ir/ActivityScopes/EconomicZones/Pages/Jahrom.aspx</ref>\n\n==Education==\n[[File:\u062f\u0627\u0646\u0634\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u0639\u0644\u0648\u0645 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u06a9\u06cc \u062c\u0647\u0631\u0645.jpg|250px|thumb|[[Jahrom University of Medical Sciences]], medical school]]\n===Colleges and universities===\nuniversities in city include:\n*[[Jahrom university]]\n*[[Jahrom University of Medical Sciences]] \n*[[Islamic Azad University, Jahrom Branch]]\n*[[Payame Noor university of Jahrom]]\n*Andisheh University\n*University of Applied Science and Technology Agriculture branch\n\n==Health==\n[[File:Jahrom motahari hospital.jpg|250px|thumb|Motahari hospital]]\n===Hospitals===\n*Peymanieh hospital\n*Motahhari hospital\n*Seyyedoshshohada hospital\n*Aboutalebi heart hospital<ref>[https://www.worldi.ir/7126 Hospitals of Fars province]</ref>\n\n===Medical centers===\n* Khatam ol-Anbia Cancer center\n* Javad ol-Aemeh Chemotherapy center\n* Honari Infertility Center\n* Hakim Salman Infertility Center\n* Honari speciality clinic\n* Emam Reza speciality clinic\n* Dental speciality clinic\n\n==Transport and communications==\n===Communication roads===\nThe most important roads in Jahrom are:\n*Jahrom-Shiraz highway \n*Jahrom-Lar under construction highway\n*Jahrom-Fasa road\n*Jahrom-Qir road\n*Jahrom-Khavaran-Sarvestan road\n*Jahrom-Hakan road\n*Jahrom-Simakan-Meymand road<ref>[http://www.iribnews.ir/fa/news/1974617/%D8%A8%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%DB%B8-%DA%A9%DB%8C%D9%84%D9%88%D9%85%D8%AA%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%A8%D8%B2%D8%B1%DA%AF%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%B4%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B2 IRIB news]</ref><ref>[http://www.irna.ir/fars/fa/News/82892807 IRNA]</ref>\n\n===Airport===\n[[File:Jahrom Airport.jpg|thumb|220px|[[Jahrom Airport]]]]\n[[Jahrom Airport]], established in 1969, has weekly flights to Tehran [[Mehrabad Airport]] and [[Mashhad Airport]].<ref>[https://www.yjc.ir/fa/news/6535132/%D8%A8%D8%B1%D9%82%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%AA%D9%87%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D9%88-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%DA%A9%D8%B3 Tehran-Jahrom flights]</ref>\n\n===Railway===\nThere is an under construction railway project Connecting Shiraz to Bandar abbas which will have a station in Jahrom.<ref>[http://mldl.ir/?p=42335 Milad Larestan magazine]</ref>\n\n===Bus terminal===\nShahid Rahmanian is the bus terminal of Jahrom with daily buses to Shiraz, Tehran, Bandar abbas, Lar, etc.\n\n{{wide image|\u063a\u0627\u0631 \u0633\u0646\u06af \u062a\u0631\u0627\u0634\u0627\u0646.jpg|800px|A panorama of Jahrom near [[Sangtarashan cave]]}}\n\n==Notable Jahromis==\n* [[Barbad]], one of the first musicians in the world\n*[[Mohammad-Javad Azari Jahromi]], Iranian [[Ministry of Information and Communications Technology of Iran|Minister of Information and Communications Technology]]\n*[[Mohammad Jahromi]], former Iranian [[Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs (Iran)|minister of labour and social affairs]]\n*[[Ali Mohammad Besharati]], former Iranian [[Ministry of Interior (Iran)|Minister of Interior ]]\n*[[Mehdi Shabzendedar Jahromi]], Iranian\u00a0[[Shia]]\u00a0jurist and member of the\u00a0[[Guardian Council]]\n*[[Seyyed Hossein ayatollahi]], Shiite clergyman and\u00a0Ruhollah Khomeini's\u00a0Representative in\u00a0jahrom. \n*[[Abd al-Husayn Lari]], clergymen and jurists of South Iran\n*Lotfollah Dezhkam,\u00a0Ayatollah,\u00a0Friday leading prayer\u00a0of [[Shiraz]] and Representative of [[Guardianship of the Islamic Jurist|Guardian of the Islamic Jurist]] in [[Fars province]]\n*Mohammadreza Rezaei Kouchi, Representative of [[Iranian parliament]] and head of the civil commission of the parliament\n*Mirza Nasir Jahromi, Iranian architect and poet\n*Jahan, Persian singer\n*Sadroddin Zahed, Iranian director, actor and translator\n*[[Ali-Mohammad Khademi]], former general manager of\u00a0[[Iran Air]]\n*[[Ali Torab Jahromi]], Iranian poet\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery mode=packed heights=175px>\nfile:Sangshekan.JPG|Inside of [[Sangtarashan cave]]\nfile:\u0628\u0627\u063a \u0646\u062e\u0644\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u062c\u0647\u0631\u0645.JPG|Palm trees in Jahrom\nfile:Qalat Jahrom.jpg|[[Qalat, Jahrom]]\nfile:\u067e\u0627\u0631\u06a9 \u062c\u0646\u06af\u0644\u06cc \u062c\u0647\u0631\u0645.JPG|City park\nfile:Mina ranjbaran.jpg|House of Toufan\nfile:Charsouq-stitched (cut 2).png|[[Jahrom Bazaar]]\nfile:Chatiz, Jahrom.jpg|Chatiz forest\nfile:Jahrom_005.JPG|Shrine of [[Abd al-Husayn Lari]]\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikivoyage}}\n{{Commons category}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20051027131123/http://www.jahrom.ir/ municipality of Jahrom]\n\n{{Fars Province}}\n{{Jahrom County}}\n\n[[Category:Jahrom]]\n[[Category:Jahrom County]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Jahrom County]]\n[[Category:Cities in Fars Province]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the administrative subdivision|Jahrom County}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name =Jahrom\n|native_name = \u062c\u0647\u0631\u0645\n| nickname                        =The Green Umbrella, Dar ol-Momenin, City of Sour Gold, Land of Palms and Oranges\n|settlement_type        = City\n|image_skyline =jahrom wiews.jpg\n|imagesize =250px\n|image_caption = from top to bottom, left to right : [[Sangtarashan cave]], Jahrom bazaar, Jahrom fire temple (Qadamgah), Chamran square, Emamzadeh Hossein, Jahrom skyline\n|pushpin_map            =Iran\n|mapsize                =150px\n|subdivision_type       = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}}\n|subdivision_type1 =[[Provinces of Iran|Province]]\n|subdivision_name1 =[[Fars Province|Fars]]\n|subdivision_type2 =[[Counties of Iran|County]]\n|subdivision_name2 =[[Jahrom County|Jahrom]]\n|subdivision_type3 =[[Bakhsh]]\n|subdivision_name3 =[[Central District (Jahrom County)|Central]]\n|leader_title           = \n|leader_name            = \n|established_title      =\n|established_date       = \n|area_total_km2         = 30\n| area_rank = 2nd\n|area_footnotes         = \n|population_as_of       = 2016 Census\n|population_urban       = 141,634 <ref>https://www.amar.org.ir/english</ref>\n| population_blank1_title         = Population Rank\n| population_blank1               = 3rd\n|population_est         =\n|population_est_as_of   =\n|population_density_km2   =4,754\n|timezone               = [[Iran Standard Time|IRST]]\n|utc_offset             = +3:30\n|timezone_DST           = [[Iran Daylight Time|IRDT]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +4:30\n|coordinates            = {{coord|28|30|00|N|53|33|38|E|region:IR|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_m              = 1050\n|website                  = {{URL|jahrom.ir}}\n|area_code =  \n|footnotes              =\n}}\n'''Jahrom''' ({{lang-fa|\u062c\u0647\u0631\u0645}}, also known as '''Jahr\u016bm''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3067522}}</ref> is a city and capital of [[Jahrom County]], [[Fars Province]], [[Iran]].  At the 2016 census, its population was 141,634.<ref>{{IranCensus2016|07}}</ref> Jahrom is the biggest city in the southern half of Fars Province and the second one in whole province.<ref>{{IranCensus2016|07}}</ref>\n\nJahrom is located {{convert|170|km|mi}} southeast of [[Shiraz, Iran|Shiraz]], the [[Capital (political)|capital]] of Fars Province. Jahrom has a [[hot semi-arid climate]] and the average rainfall is about {{convert|285|mm|in}} per year. The average temperature in this city is about {{convert|20|C|F}}. The maximum temperature in summer reaches {{convert|45|C|F}} and the minimum temperature in winter reaches {{convert|-5|C|F}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.farsmet.ir/DM/Files/files/jahrom.pdf |title=Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Fars province Meteorological Organization |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref> The average height of Jahrom is about  {{convert|1050|m|ft}} above sea level. The majority of people in Jahrom are [[Persians]] and [[Shia Islam|Shia Muslims]].\n\nJahrom is one of the historical cities of Iran. The founder of the city of Jahrom, [[Artaxerxes I of Persia]], the son of [[Xerxes I]], the fifth [[Achaemenid Empire|Achaemenid king]]. [[Ferdosi]] has mentioned Jahrom many times in [[Shahnameh]], especially in the stories related to [[Ardashir I]]. There are many ancient monuments and tourist attractions in Jahrom, Such as [[Sangtarashan cave]], [[Jameh Mosque of Jahrom]], Jahrom bazaar, Khan school and fire temple of Jahrom (Qadamgah).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fafarschto.ir/ |title=Cultural Heritage, Handicrafts and Tourism Organization of Fars province |last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nJahrom, with several universities, hospitals and medical centers, is one of the academic and medical hubs of [[southern Iran]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://snn.ir/fa/news/415249/%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%82%D8%B7%D8%A8-%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%AA-%D8%AC%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A8-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%AF%DB%8C%D9%84-%D8%B4%D9%88%D8%AF |title=Jahrom is the health center of the south |last= |first= |date= |website=Students News Network (SNN) |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref> Jahrom has two industrial towns, a special economic zone, a [[dry port]], a [[petrochemical plant]], an [[Jahrom Airport|airport]], an [[Islamic Republic of Iran Broadcasting|IRIB]] center, [[customs]] and a [[combined cycle power plant]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idro.ir/fa-ir/ActivityScopes/EconomicZones/Pages/Jahrom.aspx |title= Jahrom special economic zone|last= |first= |date= |website=Industrial Development and Renovation Organization of Iran (IDRO) |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref> Jahrom has special governorate and the municipality of the city is the second municipality in Fars province in terms of history of establishment and degree of municipality after Shiraz.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://shiraze.ir/fa/news/42176/%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D9%88%DB%8C%DA%98%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%A7-%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%AA |title= Jahrom's governorate upgraded to special |last= |first= |date= |website=Shiraze |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623143007/http://www.imo.org.ir/files/rimo-ir//PDF/Unzip_amardaraje.zip/amardarajeNew/fars.pdf |title=population and year of establishment of cities in Fars province |last= |first= |date= |website=Organization of Municipalities of Iran |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nJahrom's economy is based on agriculture and industry, and its most important agricultural products are [[dates]] and [[citrus]]. Jahrom produces %1.2 of the world's dates and %6 percent of its citrus fruits every year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.irna.ir/news/80543857/%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%83%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%87-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D9%86%DA%AF%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA |title= citrus of Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mehrnews.com/news/3864142/%D8%AC%D9%86%DA%AF%D9%84-%D9%86%D8%AE%D9%84-%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B3-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%87-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%87-%D9%86%D8%AE%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85 |title=dates of Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Mehr news |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n==Name==\nThere are three theories about the name Jahrom:\n*Based on [[Kar-Namag i Ardashir i Pabagan]], in which Jahrom is mentioned as \"Zarham\";  It is probable that Jahrom means \"green space\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Jahrom' |website=Encyclopedia Iranica |url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/jahrom |access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n*Based on [[Ahmad Kasravi]], the late Iranian historians and philologist, the name Jahrom can be analyzed to render a \"warm-place\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.jahrom.org/htmls/history.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2009-12-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110206155148/http://www.jahrom.org/htmls/history.html |archive-date=2011-02-06 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*Jahrom is Consists of \"Ja\" and \"Hrom\", Ja means \"place\" and \"Hrom\" in Avestan means \"high and forbidden fortress\", which is other name of the city of Barzeh (the current [[Takht-e Soleym\u0101n]]) In [[Iranian Azerbaijan]], near the city of [[Maragheh]].\n=== nicknames ===\n\"Green umbrella\" is a nickname of Jahrom due to the resemblance of the huge masses of palm trees around Jahrom to green umbrellas.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iranboom.ir/gardesh-gari/17419-jahrom-980127-027.html |title=Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Iran Boom |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref> \"Dar ol-Momenin\" is the other nickname which means \"house of faithfuls\" because of high percentage of Islam believers in the city. \nJahrom is also known as the \"City of Sour Gold\" and the \"Land of Palms and Oranges\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.farsnews.ir/amp/13910725001135 |title=Jahrom must stay faithful |last= |first= |date= |website=Fars news |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:\u0642\u062f\u0645\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u062c\u0647\u0631\u0645.JPG|220px|thumb|right|Qadamgah in Jahrom]]\nJahrom's history goes back some 2500 years when the [[Achaemenid]]s established the [[Persian Empire]]. The establishment of the city is attributed to [[Artaxerxes I of Persia]]. The [[Sassanid]] monument of Qadamg\u0101h is located to the south of the city , experts believe the monument was constructed during the late Sasanian dynastic era (224-651 AD), and it was a Zoroastrian shrine, probably a fire temple. Jahrom is the birthplace of [[Barbod]], who became the main lyricist and musician in the court of the great Sassanid king [[Khosrau II]] (Parviz).\n\nJahrom was [[Muslim conquest of Persia|conquered by the Muslims]] in 641 or 644 after a fierce battle. \"The Valley of the Martyrs\" in west of the city was the site of this battle, which is why it is called so. As it is described in [[Fars-Nama]], Jahrom's taxes were paid to the Crown Prince during the [[Buyid]] period. In the late [[Safavid]] and early [[Zand dynasty|Zand]] periods, was the start date of planting trees in Jahrom, specially [[palm]] trees.\n\nDuring the [[Qajar]] period, the ruler of this city began to build buildings and places for urban affairs, including the construction of the bazaar, as well as numerous caravanserais and the development of the city. In 1887, Mohammad Hassan Mirza Mohandes, introduced Jahrom as the largest and most prosperous city in Persia after [[Shiraz]] and [[Bushehr]]. Etemad os-Saltanah describes Jahrom in the late [[Qajar]] period a larger city than cities like [[Qom]] and [[Kashan]].<ref name=\"encyclopedia\">{{cite web | url=https://rch.ac.ir/article/Details/7739 | title=Jahrom | publisher=Islamic World Encyclopedia | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> People of Jahrom had an important rule in [[tobacco protest]]s of 1890 and [[Persian Constitutional Revolution]] of ealry 20th century. [[Abd al-Husayn Najafi Lari]] was the Islamic leader of the city in this period.\n\nJahrom also had an important role in the [[Islamic revolution of Iran]] and was one of the 11 cities with [[Martial law]] in pre-revolution protests. [[Seyyed Hossein ayatollahi]] was the Islamic leader of Jahrom in that period. A soldier killed the military governor of Jahrom on the birthday of [[Mohammad Reza Pahlavi]] on October 6, 1978. 1,200 people of Jahrom were martyred during [[Iran\u2013Iraq War]].<ref name=\"mehromah\">{{cite web | url=http://home.mehromah.ir/fun/touring-iran/4010-Urban-arranged-in-the-East-Empire-of-Ardashir.html | title=Jahrom, a city in the east of Ardeshir's empire | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Martyrs\">{{cite web | url=https://defapress.ir/fa/news/225110/%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85-%D8%B4%D9%87%D8%B1%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%A8%D8%A7-11-%D8%B4%D9%87%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%82%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%A8 | title=Jahrom county with 11 Martyrs | publisher=Defa press | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Climate==\nJahrom has a [[hot semi-arid climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]]: ''BSh''); The average rainfall is about {{convert|285|mm|in}} per year. The average temperature in this city is about {{convert|20|C|F}}. The maximum temperature in summer reaches {{convert|45|C|F}} and the minimum temperature in winter reaches {{convert|-5|C|F}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.farsmet.ir/DM/Files/files/jahrom.pdf |title=Jahrom |last= |first= |date= |website=Fars province Meteorological Organization |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n{{Weather box\n|width=auto\n|location = Jahrom\n|metric first=yes\n|single line=yes\n|Jan record high C = 20\n|Feb record high C = 23\n|Mar record high C = 27\n|Apr record high C = 34\n|May record high C = 37\n|Jun record high C = 41\n|Jul record high C = 42\n|Aug record high C = 40\n|Sep record high C = 39\n|Oct record high C = 33\n|Nov record high C = 30\n|Dec record high C